                <text>Provenance.
1490 - 1702 San Giacomo Source: F. Rossi (1979).
1702 Parish Church, Somendenna
by 1775 - Possibly Sant'Agostino (Bergamo, Italy) Source: Andrea Pasta (1775). Description may correspond to the Getty picture.
- 1784 Giacomo Caniana Source: F. Rossi (1979).
by 1857 - Possibly Don Clemente
by 1857 - and S. Martino Maggiore Source: Ellis Waterhouse letter to Burton Fredericksen (September 14, 1974), quoting from the diary of Otto Mündler (p. 87v).
1858 - Giuseppe Baslini Source: Eastlake (1858).
- Vito Enei
before 1871 - Valentinis
before 1871 - before 1914 Private Dealer
before 1914 - 1929 Joseph Spiridon [sold, Spiridon sale, Cassirer and Helbig, Berlin, May 31, 1929, lot 67.]
- Torlonia
- 1955 Count Alessandro Contini-Bonacossi, Italian, 1878 - 1955, by inheritance within the Contini-Bonacossi family.
1955 - 1971 Contini-Bonacossi Family, sold to Spencer A. Samuels &amp; Company, Ltd., 1971.
1971 Spencer A. Samuels &amp; Company, Ltd., sold to the J. Paul Getty Museum, 1971.</text>
